Dear user/friend of the DDP,

	As you may know, the DDP makes use of "stopwords."  These
are words that the search mechanism bypasses.  The reasoning behind
this is simple and obvious: one hopes to speed up searches and one
wants to spare the user "useless" results.  On the other hand, we 
may have overlooked some words that should be included in our groups
of stopwords.  More worrisome, we may have included some that really
ought to be searchable.  (I, for one, would like to restore the
Italian word "bene" to searchable status.)  Any advice you can offer
us will be much appreciated.

